During the course we will look at the philosophical foundations of critical thinking (logic, common fallacies, etc.) and practice applying these to analyzing and reconstructing arguments in texts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to acquaint the students with the philosophical foundations of critical thinking, most common types of faulty argumentation and to give them the skills to apply both at analyzing and re-constructing different kinds of arguments.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has completed the course will know the philosophical foundations of critical thinking (logic, common fallacies, etc.) and can apply that knowledge to analyzing and reconstructing arguments in texts.
